This place has bomb Korean food. I will say, it can get pricey outside of lunch hours, so do yourself (and your wallet) a favor and go during their Lunch Special hours 11AM-3PM (currently). I will say, their meat isn't the greatest, such as the BBQ Chicken or BBQ Beef. Had it recently and there was a lot of fat on the beef...so just be warned. Anyways, make your wallet and your mouth happy here ;) (Pics are BBQ Chicken/BBQ Beef Combo, close-up of the beef, the banchan, and the cold spicy noodle.)

This is defiantly a place where regulars and those who are in the know go to eat their favorite Korean dishes.  The location is not the best and the overall appearance of the restaurant although clean does look like it needs a remodel, but the food is fantastic and at a good value as far as price goes.  Banchan is my big thing and they got good banchan.  I wouldn't say that anything was unique or different about their banchan, but it was just better then normal and showed that they put some effort into what they off as well as the quality.  A lot of places cut corners on the banchan and that drives me nuts as I feel it is a reflection of the care and attention that the Korean restaurant puts into it's food from the beginning.  We had the spicy cold buckwheat noodles, oyster jun, and beef intestine stew.  All of which were well prepared, served in a generous portions, and all very flavorful.  The staff that were working were all very friendly and attentive. They gave good service and everything was fast and efficient.  I will defiantly return to this place again and look forward to trying some of their other dishes.

I took a group of friends out for dinner last Thursday and experienced, for the first time harassment of the highest order. We sat down and ordered quite a bit of food totalling $206. The food was excellent as usual and the service was surprisingly better than normal. After paying in cash, I returned to the table and set 2-$20 bills…$40 for gratuity for our dinner (5 of us). The table was bused and the tip swept away and set on a shelf behind our seats. When we finally stood up and exited nothing out of the ordinary happened. We carpooled and parked directly across, so it was a quick trip to the car. When we all got in the cashier, the lady who I paid the bill to appeared at the driver's window demanding a tip!!! I was incredulous to say the least. Since when is a gratuity mandatory. I went back in and suddenly the $40 appeared.  What a shame and an insult to good customers. I have more than 20% and was rewarded with a false accusation. Just beware that they chase customers down demanding a tip
